29#include "archive.h"
30#include "archive_entry.h"
31#include "archive_private.h"
32
33int
34archive_filter_code(struct archive *a, int n)
35{
36 return ((a->vtable->archive_filter_code)(a, n));
37}
38
39int
40archive_filter_count(struct archive *a)
41{
42 return ((a->vtable->archive_filter_count)(a));
43}
44
45const char *
46archive_filter_name(struct archive *a, int n)
47{
48 return ((a->vtable->archive_filter_name)(a, n));
49}
50
51int64_t
52archive_filter_bytes(struct archive *a, int n)
53{
54 return ((a->vtable->archive_filter_bytes)(a, n));
55}
56
57int
58archive_free(struct archive *a)
59{
60 if (a == NULL)
61 return (ARCHIVE_OK);
62 return ((a->vtable->archive_free)(a));
63}
64
65int
66archive_write_close(struct archive *a)
67{
68 return ((a->vtable->archive_close)(a));
69}
70
71int
72archive_read_close(struct archive *a)
73{
74 return ((a->vtable->archive_close)(a));
75}
76
77int
78archive_write_fail(struct archive *a)
79{
80 a->state = ARCHIVE_STATE_FATAL;
81 return a->state;
82}
83
84int
85archive_write_free(struct archive *a)
86{
87 return archive_free(a);
88}
89
90#if ARCHIVE_VERSION_NUMBER < 4000000
91/* For backwards compatibility; will be removed with libarchive 4.0. */
92int
93archive_write_finish(struct archive *a)
94{
95 return archive_write_free(a);
96}
97#endif
98
99int
100archive_read_free(struct archive *a)
101{
102 return archive_free(a);
103}
104
105#if ARCHIVE_VERSION_NUMBER < 4000000
106/* For backwards compatibility; will be removed with libarchive 4.0. */
107int
108archive_read_finish(struct archive *a)
109{
110 return archive_read_free(a);
111}
112#endif
113
114int
115archive_write_header(struct archive *a, struct archive_entry *entry)
116{
117 ++a->file_count;
118 return ((a->vtable->archive_write_header)(a, entry));
119}
120
121int
122archive_write_finish_entry(struct archive *a)
123{
124 return ((a->vtable->archive_write_finish_entry)(a));
125}
126
127ssize_t
128archive_write_data(struct archive *a, const void *buff, size_t s)
129{
130 return ((a->vtable->archive_write_data)(a, buff, s));
131}
132
133ssize_t
134archive_write_data_block(struct archive *a, const void *buff, size_t s, int64_t o)
135{
136 if (a->vtable->archive_write_data_block == NULL) {
137 archive_set_error(a, ARCHIVE_ERRNO_MISC,
138 "archive_write_data_block not supported");
139 a->state = ARCHIVE_STATE_FATAL;
140 return (ARCHIVE_FATAL);
141 }
142 return ((a->vtable->archive_write_data_block)(a, buff, s, o));
143}
144
145int
146archive_read_next_header(struct archive *a, struct archive_entry **entry)
147{
148 return ((a->vtable->archive_read_next_header)(a, entry));
149}
150
151int
152archive_read_next_header2(struct archive *a, struct archive_entry *entry)
153{
154 return ((a->vtable->archive_read_next_header2)(a, entry));
155}
156
157int
158archive_read_data_block(struct archive *a,
159 const void **buff, size_t *s, int64_t *o)
160{
161 return ((a->vtable->archive_read_data_block)(a, buff, s, o));
162}
